## Known Projection Limitations

List ambiguities or missing Core information that may limit EpicPreparationAudit.

| Limitation | Why It Matters | Recommended Handling |
|---|---|---|

Examples:

- desired capabilities are implicit
- disposition criteria are underspecified
- architectural expectations are unclear
- dependency semantics are incomplete
- retirement criteria are not explicit
- evidence standards are ambiguous
- canonical vocabulary is ambiguous

Do not invent missing information to fix these limitations.

## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by EpicPreparationAudit:

- Treat this projection as the strategic validation frame.
- Treat the selected epic as a proposal, not authority.
- Treat repository evidence as current implementation reality.
- Determine whether the selected epic should be Realigned, Reimagined, Retired, or marked Insufficient Evidence.
- Do not rewrite the selected epic.
- Do not create milestones.
- Do not generate implementation tasks.
- Do not select another epic.
- Do not modify the roadmap.
- Do not update roadmap completion context.
- Use repository findings only to assess strategic validity.
- Compress repository observations into strategic audit findings.
- Preserve canonical vocabulary.
- Recommend Retire only when strong evidence supports it.
- Recommend Reimagine when the strategic need remains but the epic framing is wrong.
- Recommend Realign when the epic remains valid with bounded correction.
- Recommend Insufficient Evidence when safe disposition is not possible.

## Projection Integrity Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains validation semantics only.
- No selected epic content is included.
- No repository state is included.
- No current roadmap completion state is included.
- No completed epic history is included.
- No epic disposition is decided.
- Every retained statement helps validate a selected epic against repository reality.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Project Context or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Realign, Reimagine, Retire, and Insufficient Evidence are clearly distinguished.
- Repository interpretation rules are explicit.
- Retirement requires strong evidence.
- Reimagination requires evidence that the strategic need remains but the epic framing is wrong.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational, implementation, and roadmap-prioritization details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be passed into EpicPreparationAudit.
